Key Match Events: Kusal Mendis-led Sri Lanka registered their first win in the ongoing ICC Men's ODI World Cup 2023, beating The Netherlands by 5 wickets with 10 balls remaining.
The Netherlands scored 262 runs in 49.5 overs and gave Sri Lanka a target of 263 runs to win.
For the Dutch team, Sybrand Engelbrecht (70) and Logan van Beek (59) scored the most runs.
Dilshan Madushanka and Kasun Rajitha took 4 wickets each, and Maheesh Theekshana picked one for Sri Lanka.
Chasing a target of 263, Sri Lankan batters Pathum Nissanka (54), Sadeera Samarawickrama (91*), and Charith Asalanka (44) made some quality partnerships.
Post-Match Reflections: Sri Lanka's Sadeera Samarawickrama chose as player of the match.
